gomodel:SYNGO_479  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The (sub)cellular distribution of PLC beta3 is studied in mouse brain using immunocytochemistry, subcellular fractionation and immuno electron microscopy. PLC B3 was almost exclusively detected in the cerebellum. Using immuno electron microscopy (HRP and immuno gold, pre- and post embedding), PLC B3 was found in dendrites and dendritic spines (figure 5). Although mostly cytoplasmatic, considerable amount was detected at the plasma membrane. No signal was detected in the presynaptic terminal.\n\nSubcellular fractionation experiments are in line with a postsynaptic localization of PLC B3 (figure 6).\n\nThe antibody used is characterized with KO controls (western blot and immunocytochemistry, Figure 1).. Experimental description: C57BL / 6 and PLCb3-KO (Xie et al., 1999) mice at 2-3 months of\nage were used throughout the experiments. They were treated\naccording to the guidelines for the care and use of laboratory animals\nof Hokkaido University School of Medicine." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2018-01-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_479" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

